From b934dc341806360e8ff4d8fda11984b50fa6f745 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Steve <steventhanhtuan@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 16:22:53 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 08/17] task4: harvest/serve core, notes view generation +
 skills mirror

Per-agent sha256 manifest under .publication/. harvest_drafts copies
agent-written or edited notes into shared state (index.md excluded,
see-also stub stripped) before any regeneration. generate_notes_view
mirrors shared notes into the worktree view with a three-way write
guard (absent / unchanged-since-last-write / already-target) so a
mid-pass agent edit is never clobbered and is harvested next pass.
stamp_verdicts writes coral_* fields only on change; unverifiable maps
to coral_verified: null so it renders [unverified], never [verified].
generate_skills_view harvests and mirrors skills verbatim, binary-safe.

Reviewed twice; two runtime-confirmed blocking bugs (clobber window,
unverifiable truthy misrender) fixed with regression tests.
684 passed, ruff clean.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
